main event: A single satellite with brightness of second magnitude star was observed in flight to the SE for 13 minutes.
interesting points: The object was positioned at 34 degrees north, 176 degrees 23 minutes west.
The object rose from 5 degrees above the west horizon and reached 30 degrees above the horizon.
No evaluation was made at the time, and additional information was requested from the sighting aircraft.
The report was processed through various military and government channels.
The brightness and position of the object were described in detail.
sighted object: single satellite with brightness of second magnitude star
